job_description: Contract and Data Analyst (Data Team) - job post SBCS Corporation 43 reviews Chula Vista, CA $65,000 a year -  Full-time, Contract Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $65,000 a year Job Type Full-time Contract Description: Type: Regular Full-Time Location: Remote/Hybrid (remote with the possibility of being on-site) Status : Non Exempt Pay: $31.25 ($65,000 annual salary) Negotiable This position is currently remote with the possible option of returning to a hybrid/on-site model in the future. Candidate must reside or be willing to relocate to San Diego County, California. RESPONSIBILITIES: Under the direct supervision of the Data Manager and Contract and Data Management Director, the Contract and Data Analyst is responsible for providing a critical service, which ensures that the community receives quality care and support from SBCS. Duties will include creating and maintaining reports and procedures to support program specific reporting requirements. This includes, but is not limited to data cleaning, data analysis, and troubleshooting data errors. This position work in partnership with fellow staff in the preparing reporting data for various SBCS programs. The Contract and Data Analyst is responsible for agency data quality and management, which includes working with SBCS programs and departments on data collection, data cleaning, reporting, development and maintenance of policies and procedures, in order to fulfill all contractual obligations. DUTIES: Assist Departments with contract data management for SBCS programs and subrecipients- Support SBCS Program Directors in maintaining program outcome data, working together to ensure data cleanliness, on time and on point reporting, adherence to contract requirements, and collaboration with program partners. Ensure subrecipients Efforts to Outcomes (ETO) data compliance. Provide ongoing data monitoring. Maintain data security standards. Communicate regularly with technical, applications and operational staff to ensure database integrity and security; including adherence to data privacy laws and policies such as, HIPAA and FERPA. Assist in the development and implementation strategy for data collection and cleaning. Run data scrubbing reports through internal data system(s) for SBCS and subrecipients; assist in on-going data scrubbing tasks; identify data inconsistencies and discrepancies. Ability to clean and analyze data, create reports and visual representations based on findings. Assist Contract and Data Management Department with ETO administrative duties- Establish the needs of users and monitor user access and security, control access permissions and privileges. Provide technical assistance, support, and capacity building to SBCS and subrecipients front-end ETO users. Create and update reports in ETO. Update and test new versions of ETO builds, when necessary. Ability to learn and incorporate new ETO features. SBCS Alignment- Adhere to and uphold the rigorous standards of SBCS as mandated by its mission purpose, guiding principles and standards of quality. Participate in and carry out SBCS plans/vision. Complete agency-wide annual training requirements. Other Attend and participate in required meetings and/or conferences. Ability to manage multiple projects in a fast-paced team environment. Ensure all timelines and deadlines are met. Other duties as assigned. QUALIFICATIONS: Ability to work independently and unsupervised. Proactive in communicating identifying obstacle and challenges to supervisor. Critical thinker who can identify gaps and errors in data cleaning/reporting processes and propose solutions. Responsible and accountable for own actions. Candidate must work according to the procedures, rules and regulations with the ability to recognize recurring issues and analyze their causes. Ability to maintain a clear and focused outlook under pressure. Analyze and prioritize tasks under pressure. Ability to manage multiple competing tasks and deadlines. Affinity for problem-solving and critical thinking. Detailed-oriented and focused. Willingness to take on new challenges and develop new skills. Flexible and able to quickly pivot in a changing environment. Ability to identify and adjust policies and processes, as needed. Requirements: Bachelor’s Degree or 2-4+ years of data quality/management experience. Experience with ETO software and/or data maintenance, scrubbing, reporting software is preferred. Intermediate or advanced knowledge in Microsoft Excel, Word, PowerPoint and Outlook. Must have word processing skills, including the ability to format and organize. Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Strong administrative and organizational skills. Experience with virtual meeting software is preferred. Proof of full COVID-19 vaccination required. PHYSICAL DEMANDS: Stand: Remaining on one’s feet in an upright position. Walking: Moving about on foot. Lifting: Raising or lowering an object from one level to another (includes upward pulling) 25-50 lbs. Carrying: Transporting an object, usually holding it in the hands or arms, or on the shoulder Pushing: Exerting force upon an object so that the object moves away from the force. Pulling: Exerting force upon an object so that the object moves toward the force (includes jerking) Climbing: Ascending or descending stairs, using feet and legs or hands and arms. Body agility is emphasized Balancing: Maintaining body equilibrium to prevent falling when walking, standing, crouching. Stooping: Bending body downward and forward by bending spine at the waist, requiring full use of the lower extremities and back muscles. Handling: Seizing, holding, grasping, turning, or otherwise working with hand or hands. Fingers are involved only to the extent that they are an extension of the hand. Finger Movement: Picking, pinching, or otherwise working primarily with fingers rather than with the whole hand or arm as in handling Talking: Expressing or exchanging ideas by means of the spoken word. Talking is important for those activities in which workers must impart oral information to clients or to the public, and in those activities in which they must convey detailed or important spoken instructions to other workers accurately, loudly, or quickly. The statements contained herein describe the scope of the responsibility and essential functions of this position, but should not be considered to be an all-inclusive listing of work requirements. Individuals may perform other duties as assigned. Nothing in this job description restricts management’s right to assign or reassign duties and responsibilities to this job at any time unless restricted by a negotiated contract. At-Will Employment Status Please note that all employment with SBCS Corporation (SBCS) is at-will, which means your employment may be terminated at any time by you or SBCS, without cause or advance notice. The terms and conditions of any employment may also be modified. Equal Employment Opportunity We are an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Equal Opportunity Employer/Program – Auxiliary aids and services are available upon request to individuals with disabilities. Contract Business Analyst - job post Eversheds Sutherland 39 reviews San Diego, CA 92130 $40 - $80 an hour -  Contract Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $40 - $80 an hour Job Type Contract We have an exciting opportunity for a Contract Business Analyst at Eversheds Sutherland (US) LLP. We are searching for someone who wants to be a valued contributor and member of a talented and dynamic team of lawyers, paralegals and staff. The Contract Business Analyst is responsible for the requirements from elicitation to implementation ensuring the end solution meets the business needs. The Contract Business Analyst works closely with internal customers and IT teams to define, manage and document requirements for several concurrent initiatives. Responsibilities and Duties: Gathers, understands, analyzes, and documents the need of project stakeholders, formalizing the needs into a set of actionable business requirements. Analyzes, evaluates, and documents the current business processes and identifies future state, including business process modeling. Leads and completes vendor and software selection assessment, as needed. Schedules, plans, and leads requirement gathering and review meetings. Documents and communicates key decisions and actions items. Partners on development and implementation of standard business analysis tools and methodologies with BA team and PMO Manager. Monitors cross-functional deliverables ensuring timely completion of requirement analysis and solution design. Supports change management. Researches and reviews up-to-date business processes and new IT advancements to make systems more modern. Engages with stakeholders at all levels. Performs user acceptance testing. Delivers engaging, informative, well-organized presentations to project sponsors and team members. Clearly communicates project issues and proposed mitigations to stakeholders and management. Collaborates with project managers and cross-functional teams throughout the project implementation cycle, as needed. Manages competing resources and priorities. Coordinates the day-to-day operational aspects of an initiative with PMO Manager. Applies and understands the full analysis process: Defining scope Identifying project benefits Developing business cases Requirements elicitation and management Process optimisation Business change management Requirements tractability to business benefits Input into testing Facilitating user acceptance testing Benefits realization Other duties as assigned. Knowledge, Skills and Abilities: A Bachelor’s degree is required in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business Administration, or related field, from an accredited college or university or an equivalent combination of an Associate degree with related job experience. Required Certifications: Industry recognized Business Analyst Certification (CAP or PBA or IIBA etc.) or Project Management Certification (PMP, SCM etc.) Five-seven years of experience working in a Technology Department is required, with a preference given for work experience in a multi-office legal environment. A minimum of five years of experience in leading projects as a business analyst. Familiar with software development methodologies such as Waterfall and Agile Excellent interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills are required. Detail-oriented and organized. Ability to multi-task and prioritize workloads. Ability to present ideas in a business-friendly and user-friendly language. Strong problem solving and decision-making skills. Excellent computer skills and knowledge of MS Office Suite with proficiency in Outlook are required. Salary is commensurate with years of experience and geographic location. The hourly rate for this position will be $40-80/hr. Eversheds Sutherland (US) LLP is committed to promoting diversity and inclusion within our Firm and in the larger legal profession. We believe that diverse skills, knowledge and viewpoints make us a stronger firm. Position is on-site in San Diego CA Responsibilities: Analyzes business or operating procedures to devise the most efficient method of accomplishing the work. Fully participates in impact studies, cost/benefit analyses, dependency models, and employs appropriate project tracking methodologies. Capable of conducting root-cause, corrective action analysis. Possess a working knowledge of statistics and is able to assess correlation. Able to produce visualizations to communicate findings through the use of tables and charts. Working knowledge of the training and provider organization processes that generate PESTO readiness. Supports TMS Team leadership, including Commodore/MAG CO, PMA, IWST/WSM, FRC, etc. Working knowledge of the training of Naval Aviation maintenance and supply processes and their data systems (i.e., NAMP, P-485, OOMA/DECKPLATE, AMSRR, RSUPPLY, AFAST, ACES, TFMMS, SHARP/MSHARP, PSILS, and ASM).
